{
  "stem": "2581.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had first-- and there was one time, for a long time, that I was taken to work at night for a company called Firme Moll.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now this had to do with--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Moll, M-O-L-L.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, they are out-- they're out of Munich.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "L-L, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Moll, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think they're still in business today.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we went deep underground.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think they were-- had to do something with the fire, too, with the rockets because it was a very strong construction of steel wires and cement, and my work-- my job was to carry sacks of cement, open them up, and pour it into [INAUDIBLE] big container.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And doing that all night, that-- the dust from the-- from the cement went into my eyes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I had a mark for a long time-- a hole, literally-- in my shoulder.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the-- and the sacks, where we emptied, I would put around my legs and my body to keep me war-- to keep me warm.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember, the one time I worked with my fa-- with my father together.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Somehow we managed always to work in the same place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were lucky with this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And one night, there was a Polish loco-- locomotive driver that kept bringing raw materials, the cement.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my father recognized him-- someone that he was in the army with-- and he gave him a few [INAUDIBLE] boiled potatoes.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was like giving an injection of life-- a gift of life at that time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But soon what happened is that most of the people started to get sick in the camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And as the dead were carried out, they kept bringing in more and more new people from other camps, or newer-- from other countries.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
